      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Leg Up On Sunday Readers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edwin A Turner Jr letter credits home delivery for early discovery of March 2 article about Jersey Mike's franchise in Wall, NJ (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>On a Saturday in March, I was reading the Sunday Times as my wife drove from Plainfield to Spring</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>On a Saturday in March, I was reading the Sunday Times as my wife drove from Plainfield to Spring</p>
        <p>Lake. It was lunchtime and we called ahead to order from Jersey Mike's in Wall. Just as we rolled up to the shop, I finished a article about the chain in the New Jersey Section (''With this Franchise, the State Is on a Roll,'' March 2). The sister of the owner handed me the sandwich and I mentioned the article. They had not yet seen it. One more clear advantage to home delivery.</p>
        <p>EDWIN A. TURNER JR.  Plainfield</p>
      </block>
